-- Stonecap Hires Vallance, Imperial Capital Adds Shoan, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-06-21T19:06:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-21/stonecap-hires-vallance-imperial-capital-adds-shoan-vlaad-says.html
Stonecap Securities Inc. hired   Vic Vallance as managing director and co-head of research from
Fraser Mackenzie Ltd. where he was director and head of energy
research, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Stonecap also added Christopher Barnes from Fraser Mackenzie
where he was vice-president, institutional sales.  * National Bank Financial hired Andrea Rubakovic as a real
estate investment banking associate from Salman Partners Inc.,
where she was a research analyst of Canadian agriculture and
fertilizers.  * Aminul Haque joined MGI Securities in Calgary,  Alberta , as a
research analyst from Stonecap.  * GMP Securities LP in Calgary hired Andrew Gannon as an oil and
gas research associate from Stonecap where he was an investment
banking associate.  * Imperial Capital Group Ltd. added Harj Shoan as a principal.
Shoan moved from Morgan Stanley in the U.K. where he was an
executive director with its private equity group.  * Dave Irwin joined Standard & Poor’s Capital IQ as a director
of business development from Global Maxfin Capital Inc. where he
was vice president, electronic trading.  * Erica McGuiness joined Sequeira Partners Inc. in  Vancouver  as
an associate. Prior to joining, she was an analyst with Ernst &
Young Orenda in corporate finance.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
